Immediately, for the non-interacting term we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-\bar{h}_{b\alpha}\rho_{a\alpha}^{\text{eh}}-\bar{h}_{a\alpha}\rho_{\alpha b}^{\text{eh}}=-\boldsymbol{\rho}_{\text{eh}}\bar{\boldsymbol{h}}^{T}-\boldsymbol{\rho}\bar{\boldsymbol{h}}\boldsymbol{\rho}_{\text{eh}}
\]

\end_inset

For the interaction terms we perform a mean-field decoupling on the 4-operator
 terms, reading
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
 & +\frac{1}{2}\left(V_{\beta\gamma}^{\alpha b}-V_{\beta\gamma}^{b\alpha}\right)\left(\rho_{\beta\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\rho_{a\gamma}^{\text{eh}}-\rho_{\gamma\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\rho_{a\beta}^{\text{eh}}+\rho_{a\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\rho_{\gamma\beta}^{\text{eh}}\right)+\frac{1}{2}\left(V_{\beta\gamma}^{\alpha a}-V_{\beta\gamma}^{a\alpha}\right)\left(\rho_{\alpha b}^{\text{hh}}\rho_{\gamma\beta}^{\text{eh}}-\rho_{\beta b}^{\text{eh}}\rho_{\gamma\alpha}^{\text{ee}}+\rho_{\gamma b}^{\text{eh}}\rho_{\beta\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\right)
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The fist term reads as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
 & \frac{1}{2}\rho_{a\gamma}^{\text{eh}}\left(+\left(V_{\beta\gamma}^{\alpha b}-V_{\beta\gamma}^{b\alpha}\right)-\left(V_{\gamma\beta}^{\alpha b}-V_{\gamma\beta}^{b\alpha}\right)\right)\rho_{\beta\alpha}^{\text{ee}}+\frac{1}{2}\rho_{a\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\left(V_{\beta\gamma}^{\alpha b}-V_{\beta\gamma}^{b\alpha}\right)\rho_{\gamma\beta}^{\text{eh}}\\
= & -\rho_{a\gamma}^{\text{eh}}\left(\Sigma^{\text{HF}}\right)_{b\gamma}^{\text{ee}}+\frac{1}{2}\rho_{a\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\left(\Delta_{\alpha b}^{\text{eh}}-\Delta_{b\alpha}^{\text{eh}}\right)=-\boldsymbol{\rho}_{\text{eh}}\left(\boldsymbol{\Sigma}_{\text{ee}}^{\text{HF}}\right)^{T}+\boldsymbol{\rho}_{\text{ee}}\boldsymbol{\Delta}_{\text{eh}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

and the second one as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
 & \frac{1}{2}\left(V_{\beta\gamma}^{\alpha a}-V_{\beta\gamma}^{a\alpha}\right)\rho_{\gamma\beta}^{\text{eh}}\rho_{\alpha b}^{\text{hh}}+\frac{1}{2}\left(-\left(V_{\beta\gamma}^{\alpha a}-V_{\beta\gamma}^{a\alpha}\right)+\left(V_{\gamma\beta}^{\alpha a}-V_{\gamma\beta}^{a\alpha}\right)\right)\rho_{\gamma\alpha}^{\text{ee}}\rho_{\beta b}^{\text{eh}}\\
= & \frac{1}{2}\left(\Delta_{\alpha a}^{\text{eh}}-\Delta_{a\alpha}^{\text{eh}}\right)\rho_{\alpha b}^{\text{hh}}-\left(\Sigma^{\text{HF}}\right)_{a\beta}^{\text{ee}}\rho_{\beta b}^{\text{eh}}=-\boldsymbol{\Delta}_{\text{eh}}\boldsymbol{\rho}_{\text{hh}}-\boldsymbol{\Sigma}_{\text{ee}}^{\text{HF}}\boldsymbol{\rho}_{\text{eh}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

Finally, the complete reduced density matrix equation of motions yields
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
i\hbar\frac{d}{dt}\boldsymbol{\rho}=\left[\mathbf{H}_{\text{BdG}},\boldsymbol{\rho}\right]
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where we rewrote this expression in terms of an effective Nambu Hamiltonian
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{H}_{\text{BdG}}$
\end_inset

 defined as
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\mathbf{H}_{\text{BdG}}=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
\mathbf{H}_{\text{HF}} & \boldsymbol{\Delta}\\
\boldsymbol{\Delta}^{*} & \mathbf{H}_{\text{HF}}^{T}
\end{array}\right]\label{eq:H_BdG-1}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

which is, as intended, in the same form as in Eq.(
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ref{eq:HBdGg}}$
\end_inset

) but instead with a Hartree-Fock Hamiltonian.
